    {
      "id": "9adffdf1_1cec3dba",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dmaap/charts/dmaap-data-router/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 25,
      "message": "as long as the filebeat container section in deployment.yaml points to /var/log/onap we should be good - the emptydir PV shared between the 2 containers can be mounted to a different directory on the main container - you can manually see logs in either container - but the filebeat container ships the logs to logstash\n\nAs a test I recommend you post results of a call/event/rest-call that produces a log - check it appears in both containers and then query for some text in it in kibana - like so for port 30253\n\nhttp://openlab13.onap.info:30253\n\nI will need to do this anyway to mark dmaap as passing pairwise testing.\n\nmarking -1 until the following test resutls\n\nkubectl get pods --all-namespaces\noom/kubernetes/robot$ sudo ./ete-k8s.sh onap health\n\nand a past of port 30253\n(you will need to bring up the log pod to get the 3 logstash, elasticsearch and kibana containers)\n\nthank you",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1077,
        "name": "Michael O'Brien",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "frank.obrien@amdocs.com",
        "username": "michaelobrien"
      },
